William Morrison Supermarkets Plc
may say next week that it intends to buy back 1 billion pounds
($1.6 billion) of shares over the next two years, the Financial
Times reported, citing people familiar with the matter. The
company may also announce a new dividend policy that would cost
it about 100 million pounds over two years, the newspaper said,
citing analysts at  Royal Bank of Scotland Group Plc , Morrisonâ€™s
broker.  The company, which is due to report its annual results on
March 10, declined to comment, the FT said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
